  "message": "fix(writing/wills): visualization copy consistency and mobile responsiveness\n\nUpdates to components/wills-estate-visualizations.tsx covering copy\nalignment with the article's attorney-optional framing and a concrete\nmobile-overflow fix traced via a Playwright DOM walk.\n\n**Copy consistency with attorney-optional framing**\n- InstallFlowViz:\n  * GPT Pro price $200/mo -> $100/mo in step 1 subtitle.\n  * \"Cancel anytime\" subtitle -> \"Both recommended\".\n  * Pricing detail list entries switched from em-dash to \"at\" prose\n    and GPT Pro corrected to $100/month.\n- WorkingFolderViz:\n  * Section title \"wait for an attorney-ready packet\" -> \"walk away\n    with a complete, signable packet\".\n  * Subtitle \"for the lawyer who will finalize it\" -> \"for you (or\n    for an attorney, if you decide you want one in the loop)\".\n  * Middle-panel agent quote \"draft a first pass for attorney\n    review\" -> \"draft a complete first pass of the plan for you to\n    review\".\n- StackViz:\n  * Subtitle \"a package your attorney can review and sign\" -> \"a\n    complete, signable plan (with an attorney-ready handoff packet\n    tucked in, if you want it)\".\n  * Output-package heading \"Complete estate plan package \u2014 ready for\n    your attorney to sign\" -> \"Complete, signable estate plan\n    package\" (em-dash removed).\n  * Output-package body reframed: \"you can execute it directly or,\n    if you choose, hand the Attorney Engagement Brief to a lawyer\".\n- WorkingFolderViz folder summaries:\n  * drafts: \"ready for attorney review\" -> \"ready to sign or to hand\n    to an attorney for review\".\n  * audits: \"before you pay for legal cleanup\" -> \"before they\n    become expensive problems\".\n  * attorney-handoff: rewritten as \"Optional handoff packet if you\n    decide to involve an attorney...\".\n\n**Mobile responsiveness fix for DeliverablesTreeViz**\nPre-fix: at 390px viewport, the deliverables-tree section had\nscrollWidth=810 / clientWidth=356 (a ~454px horizontal overflow).\nA DOM walk pinpointed two offenders:\n1. The operating-mode chip row used `flex overflow-x-auto pb-1` with\n   `shrink-0` on each chip. That gave the parent grid item an ~800px\n   min-content width and forced the whole viz wider than the mobile\n   viewport.\n2. The stats strip used `grid-cols-4` which made each of the four\n   cells ~85px wide. The \"DELIVERABLES\" label, with text tracking\n   0.18em, needed ~100px and clipped inside its cell.\n\nFixes applied:\n- Stats strip: `grid grid-cols-4` -> `grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4`\n  (2x2 on mobile, 4x1 at sm+). All four labels now fit.\n- Operating-mode chip row: `flex gap-2 overflow-x-auto pb-1` with\n  `shrink-0` chips -> `flex flex-wrap gap-2`. Chips now wrap to\n  multiple rows instead of forcing a horizontal scroller that leaks\n  intrinsic width up the tree.\n- Outer filter grid + inner search/category grid: added `min-w-0` so\n  grid items can shrink below children's min-content width.\n\nVerification: all 7 viz sections in the article now report\nscrollWidth == clientWidth at 390px viewport. The remaining intrinsic\nwidth offenders inside the DOM walk are SPAN.truncate (intentional\nellipsis) and SPAN.sr-only (visually hidden), neither of which\nrenders visible overflow.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
